{"kind":"symbol","identifier":{"url":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNMapView\/tileLodZoomShift","interfaceLanguage":"occ"},"variants":[{"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"occ"}],"paths":["\/documentation\/maplibre\/mlnmapview\/tilelodzoomshift"]}],"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Camera based tile level of detail controls"}],"schemaVersion":{"major":0,"patch":0,"minor":3},"primaryContentSections":[{"declarations":[{"tokens":[{"text":"@property","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" (","kind":"text"},{"text":"nonatomic","kind":"keyword"},{"text":", ","kind":"text"},{"text":"assign","kind":"keyword"},{"text":") ","kind":"text"},{"preciseIdentifier":"c:d","text":"double","kind":"typeIdentifier"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"tileLodZoomShift","kind":"identifier"},{"text":";","kind":"text"}],"platforms":["iOS","iPadOS","Mac Catalyst"],"languages":["occ"]}],"kind":"declarations"},{"content":[{"type":"heading","anchor":"discussion","level":2,"text":"Discussion"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Shift applied to the Zoom level during LOD calculation"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"A negative value shifts the Zoom level to a coarser level reducing quality but improving"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"performance A positive value shifts the Zoom level to a finer level increasing details but"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"negatively affecting performance A value of zero (default) does not apply any shift to the Zoom"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"level It is not recommended to change the default value unless performance is critical and the loss"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"of quality is acceptable. A value of -1 reduces the number of displayed tiles by a factor of 4 on"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"average It is recommended to first configure the pixelRatio before adjusting TileLodZoomShift."}]}],"kind":